<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Privacy on Tech Notebook</title><link>https://wiki.deimos.fr/tags/privacy/</link><description>Recent content in Privacy on Tech Notebook</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-us</language><lastBuildDate>Mon, 28 Apr 2025 18:51:06 +0200</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://wiki.deimos.fr/tags/privacy/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Hidden (or Covert) Channels</title><link>https://wiki.deimos.fr/Canaux_cach%C3%A9s_%5C%28ou_furtifs%5C%29/</link><pubDate>Thu, 25 Sep 2008 11:58:00 +0200</pubDate><guid>https://wiki.deimos.fr/Canaux_cach%C3%A9s_%5C%28ou_furtifs%5C%29/</guid><description>&lt;p>Why worry about hidden channels? As a good paranoid, one answer could be: &amp;ldquo;they are everywhere!!!&amp;rdquo; In the case of a mild paranoia crisis, the solution would be systematic use of encryption (and cryptography by extension). Nevertheless, this cannot satisfy all needs:&lt;/p>
